<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>GearGoblin</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.4.7.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.4.7.0</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.4.7.0</Version>
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and Tonberry Tactics export pipeline. Coexists with CharacterPanelRefined, contributing the advisor + diagnostics CPR doesn't ship.</Punchline>
    <Description>GearGoblin is a BiS planner, gear inventory reader, and materia advisor for FFXIV. v0.4.7 ("Round Trip") closes the export-optimize-import loop: `/goblinimport` consumes the `GG-PLAN:v1:` strings Tonberry Tactics emits, persists them as active plans, and surfaces a per-meld checklist on the Plan tab. v0.4.7 also ships an in-window Feedback tab (pre-filled GitHub issue URL + clipboard fallback for Discord/DM, with the /goblininfo diagnostic block auto-attached) so beta reports become triagable on arrival. v0.4.6's CPR coexistence remains: CPR handles substat derivations, GG contributes the Materia Advisor and the standalone /goblin window. The full CPR-equivalent derivation suite (Crit/Det/DH/Speed/Tenacity/Piety) is still here behind ForceDerivationsOverCpr or when CPR isn't installed. Materia formulas re-derived from public datamining sources.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
